This document describes a vocabulary; in this case Timetables and Planning (Vocabulary). A vocabulary is a collection of reusable terms, more precisely classes and properties, of which their semantics is fixed by means of a label and a definition. For terms defined in this domain additional formal agreements may be defined. The formal agreements for external terms, reused in this domain, are adopted from that external source.

Summary

This vocabulary contains the terms necessary to describe the timetables and planning of public transport networks.

The terminology is based on EPIP, this is a profile on NETEX that allows, among other things, to describe timetables and stops. The terms that can be used to describe vehicle planning are based on NETEX only.

To describe timetables, we can first describe the public transport offer by means of Networks, Lines and the Routes they follow.

To describe the network topology, we can use Points to indicate how the Routes run correctly.

Patterns of loaded Journeys (the so-called ServiceJourneys) run past ScheduledStoppoints, these are the logical stops of the Network: places from where people can travel to other stops or where people can transfer to other Lines.

For the Points through which the Journeys pass (including the ScheduledStops), PassingTimes can be described, either the times along the Stops of a Line (in a particular direction) or all the PassingTimes at the stop during the day.

It is thereby possible to classify ServiceJourneys by day type (weekday, school day, etc.) and to link this to actual dates in order to create a ServiceCalendar for a school year for example.

The ScheduledStoppoints are logical stops, but it often happens that they almost coincide spatially (are within walking distance of each other) and are part of one large physical stop (the Stopplace), eg a train station.

It is also possible to describe a hierarchy of Stops (Multimodal, Unimodal, Platform). More information can also be given about the infrastructure of the Stopplace, eg the entrances and exits.

There is also terminology in this vocabulary to describe so-called Blocks. This is an important concept when planning the services of the public transport company. They are fixed sequences of Journeys, intended to deploy the vehicles (and therefore the drivers) as efficiently as possible.

These can be linked to the most suitable Vehicle Types (eg based on their Passenger Capacity) and to the Service Calendar to easily assign drivers to Blocks.

This document is an official specification of a vocabulary and provides a partial conceptual framework for certain concepts. This specification is used to specify the definition, usage, domain and range of the RDF terms within this domain. The terms defined in this vocabulary are persistent and will as result of this never disappear, neither will the definitions change except to further clarify. Terms can over time be marked as deprecated and be replaced in newer versions of this specification.

This specification of Informatie Vlaanderen is published under the license: "Model license Free Reuse - v1.0".

2. Conformance

An exchange of data, in whatever way the data exchange happens, is compliant with this vocabulary if the terminology (classes and properties) is used in such a way that it is consistent with the semantics defined in the latest version of the specification ( domain, range, definition and usage) and when no terminology out of other vocabulary is used as alternative for terminology that is defined in this vocabularium.

4. Classes

This section gives a formal definition of every class.

Class Accessibility Assessment

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#AccessibilityAssessment
Definition The accessibility characteristics of an entity used by passengers such as a Stop Place.

Class Authority

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Authority
Specialisation of
  • http://www.w3.org/ns/org#Organization
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#AuthorityOrOperator
Definition An Organisation under which the responsibility of organising the transport service in a certain area is placed.

Class Authority or Operator

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#AuthorityOrOperator
Definition An Authority or an Operator.

Usage

 Abstract class, i.e. one of its subclasses Authority or Operator should be instantiated.

Class Block

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Block
Definition The work of a vehicle from the time it leaves a Parking Point after parking until its next return to park at a Parking Point.

Class Booking Arrangement

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#BookingArrangement
Definition Information on how to book a public transport service.

Class Country

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Country
Specialisation of
  • http://purl.org/dc/terms/Location
Definition A jurisdictional geographic boundary.

Class Crew Base

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#CrewBase
Definition A place where operating employees (e.g. drivers) report on and register their work.

Class Day Type

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#DayType
Definition A type of day characterised by one or more properties which affect public transport operation.

Usage

 For example: weekday in school holidays.

Class Day Type Assignment

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#DayTypeAssignment
Definition The assignment of operational characteristics, expressed by Day Types, to particular Operating Days within a Service Calendar.

Class Dead Run

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#DeadRun
Specialisation of
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#VehicleJourney
Definition A non-service Vehicle Journey.

Class Dead Run Pattern

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#DeadRunPattern
Specialisation of
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#JourneyPattern
Definition Journey Pattern to be used for Dead Runs.

Class Destination Display

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#DestinationDisplay
Definition An advertised destination of a specific Line or Journey Pattern, usually displayed on a head sign or at other on-board locations.

Class Destination Display Variant

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#DestinationDisplayVariant
Definition Variant of a given Destination Display, as needed for different media channels (electronic, printed, audio, mobile app, etc.).

Class Direction

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Direction
Definition States the relative direction of use of a Line, e.g. "North Bound", "South Bound", etc.

Class Garage

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Garage
Specialisation of
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#AddressablePlace
Definition Facility used for parking and maintaining vehicles.

Class Garage Point

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#GaragePoint
Specialisation of
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#ParkingPoint
Definition Parking Point in a Garage.

Class Group of Entities

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#GroupOfEntities
Definition A set of Entities grouped together according to a purpose of grouping, e.g. grouping of stops known to the public by a common name.

Class Group of Lines

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#GroupOfLines
Specialisation of
  • http://fixme.com#Mobiliteitsdienst
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#GroupOfEntities
Definition Group of Lines can be used to define several kinds of PT networks and sub-networks: what is usually called a public transport network is in fact only a specific GroupOfLines and a Line may belong to several of them.

Class Group of Stop Places

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#GroupOfStopPlaces
Specialisation of
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#GroupOfEntities
Definition A grouping of Stop Places which will be commonly referenced for a specific purpose (stops inside an airport, main stops of a city, etc.).

Class Headway Interval

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#HeadwayInterval
Definition A time interval or a duration defining a headway period and characterizing Headway Journey Groups (e.g. every 10 min, every 4-6 min).

Class Journey Frequency

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#JourneyFrequency
Definition Describes a frequency at which a given Vehicle will run at a given Timing Point for a given Time Demand Type.

Class Journey Part

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#JourneyPart
Definition A part of a Vehicle Journey created according to a specific functional purpose, for instance in situations when vehicle coupling or separating occurs.

Class Journey Pattern

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#JourneyPattern
Specialisation of
  • http://fixme.com#Route
  • http://fixme.com#Transportlinksequentie
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#LinkSequence
Definition An ordered list of Scheduled Stop Points and Timing Points on a single Route, describing the pattern of working for public transport vehicles. A Journey Pattern may pass through the same Point more than once.

Usage

 Abstract class.

Class Level

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Level
Definition An identified storey (ground, first, basement, mezzanine, etc) within an interchange building or Site on which Site Components reside.

Class Line

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Line
Specialisation of
  • http://fixme.com#Mobiliteitsdienst
Definition A grouping of Routes that is generally known to the public by a similar name or number.

Class Locale

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Locale

Class Network

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Network

  • http://fixme.com#Transportnetwerk
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#GroupOfLines
Definition A named grouping of Lines under which a Transport network is known.

Class Notice Assignment

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#NoticeAssignment
Definition The assignment of a Notice to an Entity.

Class Operating Day

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#OperatingDay
Definition A day of public transport operation of which the characteristics are defined within in a specific Service Calendar.

Usage

 An Operating Day may last more than 24 hours.

Class Operating Period

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#OperatingPeriod
Definition A continuous interval of time between two Operating Days which will be used to define validity.

Class Operator

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Operator

  • http://www.w3.org/ns/org#Organization

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#ParkingPoint
Specialisation of
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#ReliefPoint

Class Passenger Capacity

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#PassengerCapacity

Class Passenger Stop Assignment

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#PassengerStopAssignment

Class Point

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Point
Definition A 0-dimensional node of the Network used for the spatial description of the Network. Points may be located by a Location in a given Locating System.

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#PointInJourneyPattern

  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#PointInLinkSequence

Class Presentation

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Presentation

Class Service Journey Link

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#ServiceJourneyLink

Service Journey Links allow Routeplanners to calculate shortest Routes more easily since a Journey is executed at a specific time (on a specific Day Type).

Class Vehicle Journey

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#VehicleJourney
Specialisation of
  • https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Journey
Definition A VehicleJourney is the defined movement of a vehicle using a specified Journey Pattern on a particular Route. By virtue of being defined for a Day Type, a Vehicle Journey is a class of journeys that would take place at the same time on each day of a specified Day Type.

Type Class

Class Via

Type Class
URI https://purl.eu/ns/mobility/timetables-and-planning#Via
Definition An optional part of a Destination Display that distinguishes different possible paths between an origin and a destination.
